<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏠 Builder Basics — The Sloped Roof (Extension · Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Variables · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Type:</strong> Extension Activity · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🧩 This is a bonus challenge, not a weekly lesson. Try it once you are happy building with loops.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Open the <strong>Sloped Roof</strong> world. Do not run it yet.</p>
<p>It builds a roof from stairs, one square <strong>ring</strong> at a time. A ring is a square outline. The program stacks 4 rings, each on top of the last.</p>
<p>Each ring is <strong>shorter</strong> than the one below. A number called <code>roof_len</code> sets the side length. It starts at 7 and loses 2 each ring. So the rings shrink and rise to a peak.</p>
<p><strong>What shape does this make? Circle one:</strong> flat square · stepped pyramid roof · single line</p>
<p><strong>Why is each ring smaller than the one below? Circle one:</strong> to step up to a peak · to get wider · to dig down</p>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Watch the Variable Change 🔢</h2>
<p>A <strong>variable</strong> is a name that holds a number. The number can <strong>change</strong> while the program runs.</p>
<p>Here it is <code>roof_len</code> — the side length of each ring. It starts at 7 and loses 2 each ring.</p>
<p>Fill in the table. The first one is done for you.</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Layer</th>
<th><code>roof_len</code> =</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Layer 1 (bottom)</td>
<td>7</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Layer 2</td>
<td>____</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Layer 3</td>
<td>____</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Layer 4 (top)</td>
<td>____</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><strong>The widest ring is at the</strong> (circle one)<strong>:</strong> bottom · top</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Think It Through ✏️</h2>
<p><strong>If <code>roof_len</code> stayed 7, what would the roof look like? Circle one:</strong> a flat box, all rings the same size · a pointed peak · a deep hole</p>
<p><strong>Which number makes the roof start wider at the bottom? Circle one:</strong> the starting 7 · the peak block · the world name</p>
<hr />
<h2>4 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Now run it for real.</p>
<ol>
<li>Open the <strong>Sloped Roof</strong> world.</li>
<li>Type <strong><code>slope</code></strong> in the Minecraft chat and press enter to run the program.</li>
<li>Watch the rings build up, getting smaller each time, until they reach the peak.</li>
</ol>
<p>Then change the starting number. Make <code>roof_len</code> start at <strong>9</strong> instead of 7, run it again, and see how the roof changes.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> (a phone is fine). Show two things:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Fill the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write your lines here, then say them in your video.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
